$interpreted: Escaping Guard: Help!!
Qing-Feng: Everything should be... okay now...
Izumi: That's hard to say.
Qing-Feng: Y-You...
Izumi: Don't be scared, Qilin Chieftain. I'm only here to say two things.
Qing-Feng: W...What?

Izumi: First thing... Hello.
Second thing...
Izumi: Goodbye.
Izumi: Now it's all up to you, buddy.
: Some days later...
Pang: (It's only been a few days, and the east is already a festering wound... Yao, what would you think about all this?)
Pang: (Yao is dead... and yet... I still feel so troubled...)
Juan-Yun: Here you are, Pang.
Pang: Juan-Yun?
Juan-Yun: I've been looking for you... Hmm? You seem upset?
Pang: I'm fine.
Juan-Yun: And yet you don't look fine to me.
Juan-Yun: Is it because I recommended you go back and help your Tiger Tribe?
Juan-Yun: I'm sorry, I thought you might not like that. And yet, with all of this disaster, we need all the help we can get.
Pang: It is my honor to help those in need.
Pang: And yet, returning to the tribe...
Pang: ...I am still an exile, as I will forever be.
Juan-Yun: Ah...
Juan-Yun: Maybe I can smooth things out between you and the Tiger Tribe, then?
Pang: I do not think that would work.
Juan-Yun: Please, after all you did for the tribe back in the tournament?
Juan-Yun: I think they can make an exception just this once.
Juan-Yun: No response?
Pang: ...I've wanted to ask you, of all the capable hands in this Alliance... why choose me?
Juan-Yun: Why so humble, Master Pang? You are the tournament runner-up! You are plently capable and then some!
Pang: (...Maybe I'm overthinking things.)
Juan-Yun: Actually, it would be nice to have some companions that see eye to eye. But, maybe that's not very realistic of me...
Juan-Yun: You seem loyal, Pang. You wouldn't abandon your own people... I think, in that way, we could get along.
Pang: Juan-Yun, you...
Juan-Yun: Yes?
Pang: Ah... nothing.
Pang: ...I'll do it. I'll return to my tribe.
Pang: If they're in need, I cannot stand by and watch them suffer.
Juan-Yun: Great, then I will go inform them. If you have any concerns, feel free to let me know.
Pang: Thank you... Now, I must go see some of my friends. Farewell...
Izumi: I'm not so sure if he bought that hook line and sinker.
Juan-Yun: As expected, he is a wise young tiger, no so easy to hoodwink.
Izumi: So then what is your plan? Find someone else?
Juan-Yun: Don't worry, everyone has their weak points.
Izumi: Come on, you just had me kill Qing-Feng for you! I deserve a good show in return!
Juan-Yun: Don't be hasty, things are only just getting started.
Izumi: Hmm...
Izumi: Butterflies aren't like us, their lives are fleeting.
Juan-Yun: ......
Izumi: What's with that look on your face?
Juan-Yun: ...And since their lives are so short, there's no need to rush them. Let them spread their wings and fly...
Izumi: Oh yeah? Then why bribe that merchant, or kill her people? Even pretending to die?
Izumi: You made her hate the Alliance, made her into the arbiter, had her destroy the Udumbara herself...
Juan-Yun: ......
Izumi: Why don't you just wait and see if her attack really does awaken the Monster of Judgement?
Izumi: Then you won't have to kill her, right?
Juan-Yun: You misunderstand me... This is simply a matter of convenience.
Izumi: Stop pretending. Just killing her servant would be enough... you really like her, don't you?
Juan-Yun: Ugh, is it that obvious...?
Izumi: Come on, how long have we known each other? I know you've got feelings.
Juan-Yun: Yes, I suppose... I should really change that.
Juan-Yun: ...Eight.
Izumi: What?
Juan-Yun: ...I have no regrets.
Juan-Yun: If I could do it all over again, I'd do it all the same.
Izumi: ...Yeah, I wasn't doubting you.
Juan-Yun: I know, you're just worried about it.
Juan-Yun: ...But...
Juan-Yun: ...It's too hard this time. More so than any other time.
Juan-Yun: ......
Izumi: Alright already, I can't take you like this.
Izumi: You're a big boy, I don't want to see you all broken hearted.
Izumi: The eclipse has passed, the True Sun should change to someone new soon. Judging from all you've done, I think that body will be yours.
Juan-Yun: ...The True Sun? Whether it is me or not isn't important right now.
Juan-Yun: The important thing is, our road home is finally almost open...
Ru-Yi: I wanna go home!!
Ru-Yi: Why are there monsters everywhere!?
Hanbei: I told you we shouldn't travel somewhere so far away! Now look what happened, it's a mess!!
Sophie: Well how was I supposed to know it'd be monster city here! What a pain, my clothes were all so expensive!
Hanbei: Why'd you stop!?
Sophie: Look!
Sophie: Prince!?
